{"_id": "19225544|None", "id": "19225544", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J. Invest. Dermatol.; 2009 Aug; 129(8) 1921-6. doi:10.1038/jid.2008.456", "year": "2009", "article-id_pmc": "PMC2877485", "type": "title", "authors": "McDougal KE, Fallin MD, Moller DR, Song Z, Cutler DJ, Steiner LL, Cutting GR", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Variation in the lymphotoxin-alpha/tumor necrosis factor locus modifies risk of erythema nodosum in sarcoidosis.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "4049;7124", "type": "Gene"}, "text": "lymphotoxin-alpha/tumor necrosis factor", "locations": [{"offset": 17, "length": 39}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D004893", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "erythema nodosum in sarcoidosis", "locations": [{"offset": 80, "length": 31}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 113, "text": "Sarcoidosis is a multi-system inflammatory disease with organ involvement that varies by race and sex. Family studies indicate that genes play a role in the etiology and extent of organ involvement in sarcoidosis. In this study, we evaluated whether 25 variants distributed in 19 genes with a known role in inflammation were associated with erythema nodosum status in 659 sarcoidosis patients and 658 controls from A Case-Control Etiologic Study of Sarcoidosis (ACCESS). We found no association with affectation status; however, a variant in the promoter of tumor necrosis factor (TNF) at position -308 was found to be associated with erythema nodosum in Caucasian sarcoidosis patients (study-wide P=0.027). When separated by sex, a variant in intron 1 of lymphotoxin-alpha (LTA), a gene adjacent to TNF, was associated with erythema nodosum in female Caucasian sarcoidosis patients (study-wide P=0.027). These DNA variants frequently occur together in Caucasians, and each variant has individually been associated with erythema nodosum in sarcoidosis patients. These results confirm that variation in the LTA/TNF gene cluster modifies a major skin manifestation of sarcoidosis and may explain the higher rate of erythema nodosum in females with sarcoidosis.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012507", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Sarcoidosis", "locations": [{"offset": 113, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012507", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "sarcoidosis", "locations": [{"offset": 314, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007249", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "inflammation", "locations": [{"offset": 420, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D004893", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "erythema nodosum", "locations": [{"offset": 454, "length": 16}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012507", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "sarcoidosis", "locations": [{"offset": 485, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 497, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012507", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "Sarcoidosis", "locations": [{"offset": 562, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "7124", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "496"}, "text": "tumor necrosis factor", "locations": [{"offset": 671, "length": 21}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "7124", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "496"}, "text": "TNF", "locations": [{"offset": 694, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D004893", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "erythema nodosum", "locations": [{"offset": 748, "length": 16}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D012507", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "sarcoidosis", "locations": [{"offset": 778, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species"}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 790, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "40", "infons